    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`getcompletiontype()` returns an empty string for commands such as `:find`, `:sfind`, and `:tabfind` when using 'findfunc', even though these commands use `file_in_path` completion according to `:h :command-completion` and `'path'`.\n\nThis works correctly when 'findfunc' is an empty string (default value).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nfunction _G.FindFiles(arglead)\n  local files = vim.fn.systemlist('rg --files')\n  local matches = vim.fn.matchfuzzy(files, arglead)\n  return #matches > 0 and matches or files\nend\nvim.opt.findfunc = 'v:lua.FindFiles'\n\n-- or simply vim.opt.findfunc = 'foo'\n```\n\n```\n:= vim.fn.getcompletiontype('find ') -- returns ''\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```\n:= vim.fn.getcompletiontype('find ') -- returns 'file_in_path'\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-569+g1be55d02f5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.47\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-22T13:27:36Z",
